'''Shella Whent''' is an unseen character mentioned in the [[Season 1|first season]]. She is discussed by [[Catelyn Stark]] and [[Willis Wode]] in &quot;[[Cripples, Bastards and Broken Things]]&quot;. Lady Shella Whent is the head of [[House Whent]] and the Lady of [[Harrenhal]].

sections.Biography:
===Background===
Lady Shella Whent is an old woman. She's a loyal vassal of [[Hoster Tully]], the Lord of [[Riverrun]].

===[[Season 1]]===
To take [[Tyrion Lannister]] prisoner at the [[Inn at the Crossroads]], [[Catelyn Stark]] asserts her origin as a daughter of [[House Tully]] and then tells a man of [[House Whent]], Ser [[Willis Wode]], that she recognizes the black bat of Harrenhal on his coat. He affirms Lady Whent's loyalty to Lord [[Hoster Tully]] or [[Riverrun]] when asked and then helps her to arrest Tyrion.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Cripples, Bastards and Broken Things]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 2]]===
During the [[War of the Five Kings]], Harrenhal is occupied by the forces of [[House Lannister]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Garden of Bones]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt; Lady Whent surrendered Harrenhal to [[Tywin Lannister]] after the [[Battle at the Mummer's Ford]].&lt;ref&gt;Season 2 bluray: War of the Five Kings feature&lt;/ref&gt;
